<HEADLINE>
FT  22 OCT 93 / International Company News: Earnings at Caterpillar surge
ahead to Dollars 96m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CATERPILLAR, the US heavy equipment and machinery manufacturer, said
third-quarter earnings, excluding a Dollars 495m tax windfall, jumped to
Dollars 96m, or 95 cents a share, from last year's Dollars 5m, or 5 cents.
The improvement follows an 18 per cent increase in sales in the US, and a 6
per cent rise in worldwide sales. Sales for the quarter were Dollars 2.8bn,
against Dollars 2.7bn a year ago.
The company said sales of agricultural, road construction, and home building
equipment in the US strengthened, but sales in Europe declined. Caterpillar
expects demand in Europe and Japan to improve during 1994.
Higher US industry demand continued to reflect increased replacement buying
because of low interest rates, growth in corporate cash flow, and generally
improving levels of economic activity. The recovery has lifted Caterpillar's
sales in the US to 50 per cent of company sales, from 45 per cent last year.
For the nine months net income was Dollars 533m, or Dollars 5.27, on sales
of Dollars 8.4bn, compared with a loss of Dollars 216m, or Dollars 2.14,
excluding extraordinary charges, on sales of Dollars 7.4bn in the same
period last year.
</TEXT>
