<HEADLINE>
FT  22 OCT 93 / International Company News: Colgate deal lifts it to leader
in liquid soap
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
COLGATE-Palmolive, the US consumer products group, is buying the liquid hand
and body soap brands of SC Johnson Wax, the privately-held US cleaning
products group, in a deal that would make it world market leader in liquid
soap.
The company also announced an 11 per cent increase in net income to Dollars
142.8m in the third quarter in spite of sluggish sales in North America and
Europe.
Colgate-Palmolive is market leader in liquid soap in the US, while Johnson
Wax is market leader in Europe and the Pacific with its Tahiti, Douss Douss,
Pouss' Mousse and Soft Wash brands.
Colgate-Palmolive said the brands it was buying had annual sales of Dollars
75m in the fast-growing market for liquid soap, a relatively recent product
innovation. It would not disclose the price of the deal but said it was not
material.
Although Colgate-Palmolive has a strong global position in consumer
products, many of its markets in the developed world are mature and it has
been looking for new areas of growth.
Worldwide sales fell to Dollars 1.82bn from Dollars 1.84bn in last year's
third quarter, but the company said they would have been 8 per cent higher
without adverse shifts in exchange rates.
Earnings per share rose 14 per cent to 89 cents.
</TEXT>
