FT  22 OCT 93 / Queen addresses Commonwealth leaders
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In a lighthearted reference to Australia's move towards republican status,
the Queen told Commonwealth leaders at a banquet yesterday she would
'certainly not be betting on how many of you will have the head of the
Commonwealth as your head of state' in 40 years. But she was confident the
Commonwealth and its ideals would survive - 'changed, adapted, maybe even
weatherbeaten, but still there, a force for peace and good government.'
