was Dollars 410, against Dollars 430, and cash cost per oz was Dollars 202,
against Dollars 224.
Profit for the nine months was Dollars 161.5m, or 57 cents, up from Dollars
109.4m, or 39 cents, on revenues of Dollars 497m, against Dollars 340m.
