<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 93 / International Company News: Tenneco earnings more than
doubled at Dollars 116m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TENNECO, the diversified US industrial company, more than doubled
third-quarter operating earnings, helped by a sharp turnround at its farm
and construction equipment division and improvements in its natural gas
pipeline operations.
Income from continuing operations advanced to Dollars 116m, or 64 cents a
share, compared with Dollars 46m, or 28 cents, in the third quarter of 1992.
Revenues were little changed from last year, at Dollars 3.2bn.
Tenneco's heavy equipment manufacturing division, Case Corporation, reversed
last year's third-quarter loss of Dollars 68m to report a Dollars 10m profit
in this year's quarter. Sales fell to Dollars 841m, from Dollars 848m in
1992.
Case, which has undergone substantial restructuring in the past two years,
will increase output in the current three months for the first time in seven
quarters.
A 30 per cent production increase will put Case's production for all of 1993
at the same level as 1992.
Mr Mike Walsh, Tenneco's chairman, said that new pricing strategies,
aggressive inventory management and quality control would continue Case's
operating improvement into 1994.
Tenneco Gas earned Dollars 94m in the quarter, up from Dollars 58m last
year, while operating income at Tenneco's chemicals division, Albright &amp;
Wilson, rose to Dollars 20m, from Dollars 15m.
The natural gas division's results were aided by a favourable rate decision
that added Dollars 34m to operating income in the third quarter.
However, the automotive parts and packaging divisions showed only marginal
income improvements, while revenues and operating income declined at the
Newport News shipbuilding division.
For the nine months, Tenneco's operating income rose to Dollars 852m, from
Dollars 680m last time.
Income from continuing operations rose to Dollars 301m, or Dollars 1.75 a
share, from Dollars 131m, or 82 cents a share, last year.
The company said that efficiency improvements had added about Dollars 170m
to operating income since January, compared with Dollars 215m for all of
1992.
